openapi: 3.0.3
info:
  title: FOI - Operator API
  version: "2.30"
  contact:
    name: OPD Integrations Team
    email: maria.girshberg@aristocrat.com
  description: |
    This OpenAPI specification was produced from the original PDF integration manuals to improve readability, searchability, and day-to-day use by business analysts, system analysts, and developers.

    This file documents only the operator-hosted endpoints called by the aggregator in the FOI integration flow.

    Sources:

    - FOI Integration User Manual, Release Version: 2.30
    - FOI Integration User Manual, Release Version: 3.0 (DRAFT, currently in progress)
    - OPD Integration Team clarifications

    This file is fully anonymized for security reasons. COMPANY stands for the company name used in the source materials.

    Disclaimer:

    The source manuals were not historically revised together with every integration change. This OpenAPI specification may therefore inherit mismatches, omissions, or outdated wording from the source materials. If you find a discrepancy or an update is required, contact Maria Girshberg at maria.girshberg@aristocrat.com.

    Authentication:

    Requests to operator endpoints that include an Account object must be authenticated with the username and password provided for the integration.

    Transport:

    The communication interface between the operator and the HUB is handled by server-to-server requests via HTTPS using POST method. Requests and responses are sent as JSON.

    Error Handling:

    If an error occurs on the operator side, the operator should reply with the correct error code.

    For errors that should be retried, operators generally use error codes above 100. For final rejection, operators generally use codes below 100.

    The following table lists the error names and the associated error codes.

    | Name | Code | Comments |
    | --- | --- | --- |
    | InsufficientFunds | 1 | Player doesn't have enough money to make a wager. |
    | InvalidNegativeAmount | 3 | Negative amount. |
    | AuthenticationFailed | 4 | Credentials provided in the API are incorrect. |
    | TokenExpired | 5 | Token is expired. Relevant only when FinancialMode = 1 (Ecommerce mode) in the AuthenticationResponse. |
    | UnknownTransactionId | 6 | Transaction ID not found. |
    | InvalidGame | 7 | Game not found. |
    | InvalidToken | 8 | Token not found. Note: This error should be returned if the token is not found in the operator system/DB. |
    | InvalidRound | 9 | Round not found. |
    | InvalidUserId | 10 | Player ID not found |
    | TransactionAlreadySettled | 11 | The debit or credit is settled already. |
    | AccountIsLocked | 12 | User account is locked. Note: This error is returned only for Authenticate, DebitCredit, and Debit methods. Actions such as canceltransaction or credit should always pass even when locked. |
    | PlayerLimitExceededTurnover | 13 | Player responsible gaming rule. |
    | PlayerLimitExceededSessionTime | 14 | Player responsible-gaming session time limit was exceeded. |
    | PlayerLimitExceededSessionStake | 15 | Player responsible-gaming session stake limit was exceeded. |
    | PlayerLimitExceededSessionLoss | 16 | Player responsible-gaming session loss limit was exceeded. |
    | RoundAlreadyEnded | 17 | Round has already ended and no more wagers or winnings can be accepted. |
    | TransactionAlreadyCancelled | 18 | The transaction has already been cancelled. |
    | PlayerHaveOpenedRounds | 19 | If the player has opened rounds for the game played (applicable to debit calls only) |
    | NoRoundsLeft | 20 | The player attempts to make a bet and doesn't have any rounds left. This is relevant only when the FinancialMode = 1 (Ecommerce mode) in the AuthenticationResponse. |
    | BetAmountUnderMinimum | 21 | The player is trying to place a bet with a bet lower than the minimum. |
    | DailyTimeLimit | 22 | When the daily time limit is reached within the game, a daily time limit message should be displayed |
    | WeeklyTimeLimit | 23 | When the weekly time limit is reached within the game, a weekly time limit message should be displayed. |
    | MonthlyTimeLimit | 24 | When the monthly time limit is reached within the game, a monthly time limit message should be displayed. |
    | RCRegulationFailed | 25 | If the regulation fails. |
    | ResponsibleGamingLimitReached | 26 | Responsible-gaming limit was reached. |
    | SessionTimeLimitReached | 27 | Spanish regulation Time limit reached |
    | SessionLossLimitReached | 28 | Spanish regulation Loss limit reached |
    | InvalidGamePlatform | 29 | Invalid game platform type |
    | InvalidCurrency | 30 | Invalid player currency |
    | GeoLocation | 31 | In order to deposit and place bets at Play Alberta, you must reside in the province of Alberta. At this time, we are unable to verify that your current location is within Alberta. |
    | InvalidGeolocation | 151 | The player geolocation is not corresponding with the defined game regulation. |
    | GeneralError | 900 | An unexpected error occurred. |

    Most responses include an Error object. In successful responses, Error is null. Some legacy or endpoint-specific error responses use flat ErrorCode and ErrorMessage fields; check the endpoint response schema before implementation.

